<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="258" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="9.[140,1108,413,580]" pageId="9" pageNumber="258">
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1850" box="[140,346,413,439]" class="Insecta" family="Haliplidae" genus="Haliplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cribrarius">
<emphasis box="[140,346,413,439]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="258">Haliplus cribrarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded from Newfoundland, Labrador, and 
<collectingRegion box="[933,1071,413,440]" country="Canada" name="Nova Scotia" pageId="9" pageNumber="258">Nova Scotia</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Matheson R" box="[140,343,448,474]" pageId="9" pageNumber="258" pagination="156 - 193" refId="ref6887" refString="Matheson R (1912) The Haliplidae of America north of Mexico. Journal of the New York Entomological Society 20: 156 - 193." type="journal article" year="1912">Matheson (1912)</bibRefCitation>
, from 
<collectingRegion box="[423,607,448,475]" country="Canada" name="New Brunswick" pageId="9" pageNumber="258">New Brunswick</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Roughley RE" box="[654,852,448,474]" pageId="9" pageNumber="258" pagination="60 - 61" refId="ref6949" refString="Roughley RE (1991) Family Haliplidae: Crawling Water Beetles. In: Bousquet Y (Ed) Checklist of Beetles of Canada and Alaska. Ottawa, Ontario: Agriculture Canada, publication 1861 / E: 60 - 61. http: // www. canacoll. org / Coleo / Checklist / PDF files / HALIPLIDAE. pdf [accessed 5 January 2009]" type="journal article" year="1991">Roughley (1991)</bibRefCitation>
, and from 
<collectingRegion country="Canada" name="Prince Edward Island" pageId="9" pageNumber="258">Prince Edward Island</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Vondel BJ van" box="[311,475,483,510]" pageId="9" pageNumber="258" pagination="1 - 171" refId="ref7251" refString="Vondel BJ van (2005) Haliplidae. In: Nilsson AN, Vondel BJ, van (Eds) Amphizoidae, Aspidytidae, Haliplidae, Noteridae and Paelobiidae (Coleoptera, Adephaga). World Catalogue of Insects 7: 1 - 171." type="journal article" year="2005">Vondel (2005)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Majka CG" box="[531,686,483,510]" pageId="9" pageNumber="258" pagination="239 - 260" refId="ref6764" refString="Majka CG (2008) Th e aquatic Coleoptera of Prince Edward Island, Canada: new records and faunal composition. In: Majka CG, Klimaszewski J (Eds) Biodiversity, Biosystematics, and Ecology of Canadian Coleoptera. ZooKeys 2: 239 - 260. http: // pensoftonline. net / zookeys / index. php / journal / article / viewFile / 25 / 37 [accessed 5 January 2009]" type="journal article" year="2008">Majka (2008)</bibRefCitation>
(
<figureCitation box="[701,768,483,510]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="9.[141,213,1623,1645]" captionText="Figure 3. Distribution of Haliplus cribrarius and Haliplus longulus in Atlantic Canada. Labrador records of H. cribrarius are shown in Figure 5." pageId="9" pageNumber="258">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). In Atlantic 
<collectingCountry box="[918,1004,483,509]" name="Canada" pageId="9" pageNumber="258">Canada</collectingCountry>
there are records from small eutrophic ponds, shallow lake margins, river margins (in association with 
<taxonomicName box="[198,264,554,580]" class="Liliopsida" family="Typhaceae" genus="Typha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="258" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[198,264,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="258">Typha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.), in a stream, and from a cattail swamp.
</paragraph>
